 -= System-X Changes =-

 Since System-X is born in the end of `96 lots of changes are
 done on this software.
 The BBS was under development by ZED for all versions 
 up to the 1.05r2

 @{" Version 1.01    " link "101" 0}
 @{" Version 1.02    " link "102" 0}
 @{" Version 1.03    " link "103" 0}
 @{" Version 1.04    " link "104" 0}
 @{" Version 1.04fix " link "104f" 0}
 @{" Version 1.05    " link "105" 0}

 Then he leave the development and gave the sources 
 out to aminet.
 I pick them up some weeks before and at that time i`m working
 more and more on the codes.

 @{"Version 1.06      " link "1.06" 0}
 Changes in the 1.06 are done carefully, coz the sources are 
 new and i have to study the powerfull envoirement 
 of the sources, before i do any bigger changes.
 
 @{"Version 1.06b     " link "106b" 0}                
 This version contains more changes to make some things 
 running better.

 @{"Version 1.06bf    " link "106bf" 0}                
 A majorbug comes in and is fixed in this version.

 @{"Version 1.07      " link "107" 0}
 [Q]uasar joined as co-developer and adds and fixes
 some neat things.
@endnode

@node "101" "Version 1.01"
 -=[ 14-June-1997 ]============[ 1.00 -> 1.01 ]===============-

        - TELNET callers no longer get a baud of 0
        - Enforcer hits removed from SX and SX-Config 
          (thanks Skittle)
        - Deleting Messages now possible
        - Quoting Messages now possible
        - Better DayDream Support 
          (WHO's ONLINE doors work, SoulFront and 
           RealTimeWho tested!)
        - SX-Config->Doors->FrontDoor feature now works 
          (tested with SoulFront)
        - "C"onfig Button added to SX-MCP
        - SX-Config->MCPPrefs Improved
        - Delete/UnDelete now functional in online UserED
        - If two new users logged in at once it would 
          screw up - fixed
@endnode

@node "102" "Version 1.02"
 -=[ 25-June-1997 ]============[ 1.01 -> 1.02 ]===============-

        - Sent-by-Lines now work
          (SX-Config->Confs "SentByLine"check boxes)

        - Background upload checker included!
          (You must enable it in each conference, SX-Config->Confs)

        - Checks userbase when entering message

        - FILE_ID.DIZ from ZIP now unpacks properly

        - Doesn't re-init modem when you open screen or press HELP
                (this could hangup on a connecting caller)

        - Pause after each screen now possible

        - ibmcon.device included. This may be used in-place of
          kalacon.device in your "Local Display" and "Display Modes"
          config. It offers fast 2/8/16 color ANSI and some VT100 support.

        - Checks for ansi's in conference path, eg:

                SX:Confs/Amiga/Commands.255.ANS
                SX:Confs/Amiga/Commands.ANS
                SX:Screens/Commands.255.ANS
                SX:Screens/Commands.ANS

                This would be the order in which it searches for the ansi.

        - Two new functions added (17 and 18), See DOC/SXFunctions.

        - It's now possible to run a filechecker door. Refer to SX.Guide
@endnode

@node "103" "Version 1.03"
 -=[ 16-July-1997 ]============[ 1.02 -> 1.03 ]=========================-

        - Screen Mode, Pens and Palette menu-options added.

        - Time left moved to title bar in HH:MM:SS format

        - Realname displayed in status bar (replaces time left)

        - The "SX" button in the bottom-right corner does something.
                (Try it when someone is online)

        - Simple AREXX interface added to SX-MCP, see REXX/ dir or
                SX.Guide for more information

        - New Full Screen Editor available - SXEd 1.03!!
                (Put "Doors:SXEd" into SX-Config->Doors->Message Editor
                        and select the "XIM /X" type)

        - File Attaching now possible (with SXEd only)

        - "Disallow Attachments" CheckBOX added to SX-Config->
                Conf/File/Msg->MessageBases.

        - Entering a message to "ALL" or "SYSOP" works again! :)

        - Full connect string logged (SX:Node%ld/CallersLog) for the
                benefit of STopCPS.

        - BGCheck Optimized

        - Experimental FAME door support added.

        - SX-MCP now has a Zoom gadget.

        - Paragon door command 203 fixed (used to crash!)

        - Some enforcer hits removed.

        NOTE:        For AREXX doors, install rexxdoor (from AmiExpress)
                into the DOORS: directory, *NOT* SX:Utils/ as previously
                written in the docs.
@endnode

@node "104" "Version 1.04"
 -=[ 27-September-1997 ]==========[ 1.03 -> 1.04 ]=======================-

        - Online UserED Bug (Presets etc) fixed.

        - Some new users would get marked as deleted - fixed

        - Quoting Messages fixed

        - You can now enter messages to "ALL" or "EALL" like /X

        - It's possible to run more than 1 filecheck door, see
          "FileCheck Door - How?" in SX.Guide for more information.

        - FullScreenEditor and BGCheck are now user configurable.
          See function 99 and 100 or the "Bonus/" directory.

        - SXEd (Message Editor) now allows international characters

        - MoveFile door added (move between filedirs and/or confs)
                (still alpha version, use at own risk)

        - SX-MCP saves your away-flag and away-reason when you quit

        - SX-MCP can shutdown all nodes when you click the close gadget

        - SX-Config -> Main -> Inactivity Timeout now works. Set it
          to a reasonable number, like 300. Set to zero to turn off.

        - When viewing messages, the message header no-longer scrolls
          away when the message is long.

        - More: (C)ontinuous option now works

        - Userlist no-longer shows deleted users

        - "D <filename>" from menu works.

        - FetchKey() DD-Door routine improved. Sick-Chat now works!

        - ShowAnsi() routine is now a bit faster.

        - SX now handles incomplete uploads and resuming much better.
          It stores incomplete uploads away and asks the user if they
          want to resume, next time they hit 'U'.

        - Some door routines have been made more compatable with /X.
          It's now possible to run "JoinCnf 3.6 - EMPiRE" with SX!
          (You must have a "J" command in your Internal-Map too!)

        - If you double click on a node in SX-MCP, it will be launched.

        - Ansi capture feature added (in the pulldown menus).

        - Doesn't allow uploads if space low.
          (Check SX-Config -> Main -> Min Upload Space).

        - You can change your (in SX:TXT/Strings.XXX)

        [P]roceed, (D)isconnect after - (A)bort:

                to:

        [P]roceed, (E)dit Flags, (D)isconnect after, (C)hange Protocol -
(A)bort:


        Note:        If you have not fixed your STRINGS.XXX control codes
yet,
                refer to "Editing STRINGS.XXX" in SX.Guide or the BBS
                may crash!!

@endnode

@node "104f" "1.04fixed"
 -=[ 03-October-1997 ]============[ 1.04 -> 1.04fix ]======================-

        - It could sometimes lockup when opening screen - fixed

        - SXEd had left/right arrows swapped - fixed

@endnode

@node "105" "1.05"
 -=[ XX-December-1997 ]==============[ 1.04 -> 1.05 ]======================-

        - New auto inserts for stdio door execution:
                        %t        timeleft (mins)
                        %a        access level (security)

        - MCI Code ~LF| now works (node number).

        - When you give users a new access-preset, timeleft is changed too.
          (Online UserED)

        - MoveFile() routine fixed - faster and safer (used during upload).

        - Local Uploading more than 1 file works again :)

        - Delete button added to GUI-UserED

        - New checkbox added to SX-Config->Conf/Msg/File->Edit Message Bases
          "Ask Private". Will ask the user if they want the message to be
          private. If ticked, this overrides "Private Area: " checkbox.

        - Serial Device and DTE Speed can be left blank for local nodes
          without crashing the node.

        - ~NP| MCI code added - turns OFF "More? (y/n/c)" prompts.

        - SX-Config -> "Local Display" touched up a bit.

        - SX can(not) allow multiple logins (check SX-Config->"This Node")

        - Local downloads now possible. Files copied to SysOp Download Path

        - "R <number>" from menu is now possible.

        - Upload.log loop bug seems to be fixed.

        - It's possible to run doors from within doors! eg: Run SXNUKE from
          AquaScan just like on /X systems.

        - BGCheck has been optimized and no longer requires c:move command.

        - BB_CHATFLAG (142) XIM-Door command now works.

@endnode

@node "1.06" "1.06"

 System-X 1.06 (eSSeXX)

 - change all version requests and strings to SX 1.06 (eSSeXX)
 - sx-config: nodeselection by a slider gadget now
 - sx-config: creating a new msgbase will create the related
              Directory, too.
 - sx-config: change Mainconfig values for Min HD Space to KB
              and the Timeout/Timeoutwarn to Minutes.              
 - sx-config: creating a new conference will create the needed Directo
              and a Directory /Messages
              creating a new MsgBase will create the needed Dirs, too.
              (confpath/Messages/BaseX)
              All that selectable with nice Reqtools requester, default
              ok.
 - sx-config: creating a new Menu will create a default Command Prompt
              too. You will be asked by a requester.
 - sx       : Inactivity Time Warning is ok now. Set the inactivity warn
              minutes in sx-config, when the pre-alarm should run.
 - sx       : change SXFunction 15 (UserList) to more options:
              Extranumber 0 : list handle, location, calls 
              Extranumber 1 : list relname, location, calls
              Extranumber 2 : list handle, axx, location, calls, lasto
              Extranumber 3 : list realname, axx, location, calls, las
 - sx-mcp   : doubleclick on the nodelist will bring up the nodescreen
              to front now. This was only able, if the screen was already
              open..
 - sx       : add SX:/TXT/OfflineHelp.ANS and bring the keys for
              online and offline nodescreen up to date. 
 - recompiled most additional utils and main`s for 020 and 000
 - began to pack the new updatearchives for 68000 and 68020, change
   some ansi and some penouts.
 - writing the guide, day by day
 - sx-config: change some penouts, string output..
 - write an Installer for the BBS, includes some features, 
   i.e. create a StartBatch. 
 - test installing, do preconfigs, ...
@endnode

@node "106b" "106b"

 System-X v1.06b (eSSeXX)

 - sx  : Commands given at LineInput() are stored in a table
         now. Recall them with the up- and down arrowkeys like
         in a shell.
         passwords are removed from command recallbuffer 

 - sx  : implement XIM-Function #517 JH_LOGONTYPE

         msg->Data -1: no node avail
                    0: awaiting call
                    1: sysop login
                    2: local login
                    3: remote login
     
 - sx  : change the JoinConference function a bit. Now join 
         first before Join.ans is typed/executed.

 - sx  : change Login credits to dIGITAL cORRUPTION

 - sx  : FileChecking: DupeFiles were not found. Fixed.

 - sx-config: fix a small gfx-bug
@endnode

@node "106bf" "106bf"
